ion, and gender ideologies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFeminismzSpainxHistoryy18th century. 0aSex rolezSpainxHistoryy18th century. 0aWomenzSpainxHistoryy18th century. 0aWomenzSpainxIntellectual life. 0aWomenzSpainxSocial conditions. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aenlightenment.  aeurope.  afemale artist.  afemale author.  afemale citizen.  afemininity.  afeminism.  agender roles.  agender studies.  agender.  ahistory.  aintellectual women.  anonfiction.  apolitical discourse.  apolitical reform.  apolitics.  apublic discourse.  asocial action.  aspanish women.  atertulias.  athe woman question.  awomen in history.  awomen.  awomens place.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093222740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520932227423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520932227/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles